Condition anaylsis

z-score T and F resids by location

Running lm(weight ~ length + …) for now for speed to get a feel for how slopes of the length/weight relationship vary across species and other variables. Will likely move to RE models next.

If newData, then will load raw files, parse, filter and save as ‘dat’

newData = FALSE
date <- "June4"  #suffix for data subdirectory

Only need to run this with new data - data output as ‘dat’

if (newData) {
    
    # bring in all of the fish size data
    fish <- list.files(paste0("D:/projects/ecoDrought/bodySize/All_Size_inputs/Size_inputs_", 
        date), pattern = "*.txt", full.names = T)
    
    txt_files_df <- lapply(fish, function(x) {
        read.table(file = x, header = T, sep = ",")
    })
    
    all_fish <- do.call("rbind", lapply(txt_files_df, as.data.frame))
    
    ## bring in the covariate data
    covs <- read.csv("D:/projects/ecoDrought/bodySize/All_Size_inputs/covariates_size_analysis.csv")
    
    # merge fish data with covariate data
    all_fish_init <- merge(all_fish, covs, by = "RALLID")
    
    # Select only those fish of interest
    
    # species of interest
    sinc <- c("Bonneville Cutthroat Trout", "Colorado River Cutthroat Trout", "Redband Trout", 
        "Bull Trout", "Brook Trout", "Mountain Whitefish", "Brown Trout", "Westslope Cutthroat Trout", 
        "Yellowstone Cutthroat Trout", "Rainbow Trout")
    
    # exclude weir data
    nw <- c("Lake", "stream")
    
    dat0 <- all_fish_init %>% filter(species %in% sinc, site_type %in% nw, !is.na(Weight), 
        Length > 75) %>% rename(weight = Weight, length = Length) %>% mutate(log10Weight = log10(weight), 
        log10Length = log10(length))
    
    # Species-specific LWE regressions so we can add residuals to dataset
    lwModel <- function(df) {
        lm(log10Weight ~ log10Length, data = df)
    }
    
    datBySpecies <- dat0 %>% group_by(species) %>% nest() %>% mutate(model = map(data, 
        lwModel))
    
    datBySpecies <- datBySpecies %>% mutate(resids = map2(data, model, add_residuals))
    
    dat <- dt_unnest(datBySpecies, resids)  # unnest() from tidyverse is so slow it never finishes
    
    dat <- dat %>% group_by(location) %>% mutate(daStd = (log(drain_area_km2) - (mean(log(drain_area_km2))))/sd(log(drain_area_km2)), 
        sFStd = (log(summerF) - (mean(log(summerF + 1e-04), na.rm = TRUE)))/sd(log(summerF + 
            1e-04), na.rm = TRUE), sTStd = (log(summerT) - (mean(log(summerT), na.rm = TRUE)))/sd(log(summerT), 
            na.rm = TRUE), slopeStd = (SLOPE - mean(SLOPE))/sd(SLOPE), rdStd = (log(rel_density) - 
            (mean(log(rel_density), na.rm = TRUE)))/sd(log(rel_density), na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
        ungroup()
    
    speciesList <- unique(dat$species)
    
    save(dat, file = paste0("D:/projects/ecoDrought/bodySize/All_Size_inputs/Size_inputs_", 
        date, "/dat.R"))
    
    rm(all_fish_init, all_fish, dat0)
}
if (newData) {
    for (i in c(1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9)) {
        print(i)
        
        ggplot(dat %>% filter(species %in% c(sinc[i])), aes(log10Length, log10Weight, 
            color = Lake)) + geom_point(alpha = 0.1) + geom_smooth(method = "lm") +

    }
}

LW relationship analysis section

Species differences

Species have significantly different LW relationships, although LW regression lines overlap considerably. No random effects yet - lmer takes a long time to run (may try bam, https://m-clark.github.io/posts/2019-10-20-big-mixed-models/)

if (newData) {

Spatially-nested lmer() by species to explore spatial structuring of variation in LW regression residuals HUC12 nested within HUC8 nested within Location

# build up hierarchical random effects for each species Hierarchical graphs for
# huc12/huc8/location
lmerModel <- function(df) {
    lmer(resid ~ 1 + (1 | location/HUC8_Name/HUC12_NAME), data = df)
}

reBySpecies <- function(mod, species) {
    re <- as.data.frame(ranef(mod))
    
    re12 <- re %>% filter(grpvar == "HUC12_NAME:(HUC8_Name:location)") %>% mutate(huc12 = str_split(grp, 
        ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 1], huc8 = str_split(grp, ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 
        2], loc = str_split(grp, ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 3]) %>% rename(condval12 = condval)
    
    re8 <- re %>% filter(grpvar == "HUC8_Name:location") %>% mutate(loc = str_split(grp, 
        ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 2], huc8 = str_split(grp, ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 
        1]) %>% rename(condval8 = condval)
    
    reLoc <- re %>% filter(grpvar == "location") %>% mutate(loc = grp) %>% rename(condvalLoc = condval) %>% 
        select(condvalLoc, loc)
    
    reAll1 <- left_join(re8, reLoc) %>% select(condval8, loc, huc8, condvalLoc)
    reAll <- left_join(re12, reAll1) %>% arrange(loc, huc8, huc12)
    reAll <- reAll %>% mutate(condvalLoc8 = condvalLoc + condval8, condvalLoc812 = condvalLoc + 
        condval8 + condval12)
    
    return(reAll)
}

hierRECharts <- function(d, species) {
    gg <- ggplot(d, aes(condvalLoc812, huc12)) + geom_point(color = "#ff9a36") + 
        geom_point(aes(condvalLoc8, huc12), color = "#3f7bc4") + geom_point(aes(condvalLoc, 
        huc12, shape = factor(loc)), color = "#bdb2a8") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0) + 
        scale_y_discrete(guide = guide_none(title = NULL)) + scale_x_continuous("Residual from species-specific LW relationship") + 
        ggtitle(species) + facet_wrap(~huc8)
    
    ggsave(paste0("D:/projects/ecoDrought/bodySize/All_Size_inputs/ecoDrought_conditionAnalysis/charts/hierResids_", 
        species, ".png"))
    return(gg)
}

## Charts of nested random effects
datBySpeciesRE <- dat %>% filter(species %in% speciesList[c(1, 3, 4, 5, 7)]) %>% 
    # filter(species %in% speciesList[5]) %>% #
group_by(species) %>% nest() %>% mutate(model = map(data, lmerModel)) %>% mutate(RE = map2(model, 
    species, reBySpecies)) %>% mutate(charts = map2(RE, species, hierRECharts))

############################################################################## some species have data for one location only #2 6 8 9 Colorado River Cutthroat
############################################################################## Trout model has singularity - ignoring for now Hierarchical graphs for
############################################################################## huc12/huc8

lmerModelNoLocation <- function(df) {
    lmer(resid ~ 1 + (1 | HUC8_Name/HUC12_NAME), data = df)
}

# build up hierarchical random effects for each species
reBySpecies812 <- function(mod, species) {
    re <- as.data.frame(ranef(mod))
    
    re12 <- re %>% filter(grpvar == "HUC12_NAME:HUC8_Name") %>% mutate(huc12 = str_split(grp, 
        ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 1], huc8 = str_split(grp, ":", simplify = TRUE)[, 
        2]) %>% rename(condval12 = condval)
    
    re8 <- re %>% filter(grpvar == "HUC8_Name") %>% mutate(huc8 = grp) %>% rename(condval8 = condval) %>% 
        select(condval8, huc8)
    
    reAll <- left_join(re12, re8) %>% arrange(huc8, huc12)
    reAll <- reAll %>% mutate(condval8 = condval8, condval812 = condval8 + condval12)
    
    return(reAll)
}

hierREChartsNoLocation <- function(d, species) {
    gg <- ggplot(d, aes(condval812, huc12)) + geom_point(color = "#ff9a36") + geom_point(aes(condval8, 
        huc12), color = "#3f7bc4") + geom_vline(xintercept = 0) + scale_y_discrete(guide = guide_none(title = NULL)) + 
        scale_x_continuous("Residual from species-specific LW relationship") + ggtitle(species) + 
        facet_wrap(~huc8)
    
    ggsave(paste0("D:/projects/ecoDrought/bodySize/All_Size_inputs/ecoDrought_conditionAnalysis/charts/hierResids_", 
        species, ".png"))
    
    return(gg)
}
